  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Consecutive patients with Crohn's disease undergoing intestinal resection of all
             macroscopic diseased bowel, with an endoscopically accessible ileocolic anastomosis;

          2. Enrolled patients must have one or more risk factor for the development of
             postoperative recurrence including penetrating disease behaviour, prior bowel
             resection, and active smoking.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Severe comorbidities;

          2. With a stoma;

          3. With malignancy;

          4. Pregnancy;

          5. Intolerant of thiopurine drugs;

          6. With contraindication of using rifaximin or thiopurine drugs.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
